"title": "2306: Jesus Christ, as high priest",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2306: jesus christ, as high priest",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Jesus Christ, being a truly human high priest, perfectly represents humanity before God. He made atonement for sins by his own sacrificial death. Being a truly divine high priest, this act of Christ's was perfect, once for all and of eternal value.</p>\n<h2>The ministry of Jesus Christ as high priest</h2>\n<h3>He made atonement for sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:17\">HEB 2:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:3\">HEB 8:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:7\">HEB 9:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:11-Heb9:12\">HEB 9:11–9:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:11-Heb13:13\">HEB 13:11–13:13</a></p>\n<h3>He represents human beings before God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:1\">HEB 5:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:34\">ROM 8:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:1-1John2:2\">1JN 2:1–2:2</a></p>\n<h3>He entered the Most Holy Place</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:24\">HEB 9:24</a></strong> <em>On the Day of Atonement the high priest entered the Most Holy Place (the sanctuary) which represented the presence of God. Jesus Christ fulfilled this ritual by entering heaven.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:14\">HEB 4:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:19-Heb6:20\">HEB 6:19–6:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:7\">HEB 9:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:12\">HEB 9:12</a></p>\n<h3>He makes believers perfect</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:14\">HEB 10:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:10\">HEB 10:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:12\">HEB 13:12</a></p>\n<h3>He brings believers close to God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:19-Heb10:22\">HEB 10:19–10:22</a></strong></p>\n<h3>He helps those being tempted</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:18\">HEB 2:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:15\">HEB 4:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:2\">HEB 5:2</a></p>\n<h3>He intercedes continually</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:24-Heb7:25\">HEB 7:24–7:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:20\">JHN 17:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:34\">ROM 8:34</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ, the human high priest</h2>\n<h3>As a man he is able to represent human beings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:17\">HEB 2:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:1\">HEB 5:1</a></p>\n<h3>He is divinely appointed</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:5-Heb5:6\">HEB 5:5–5:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:1-Heb3:2\">HEB 3:1–3:2</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ, the divine high priest</h2>\n<h3>He is sinless</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:26-Heb7:27\">HEB 7:26–7:27</a></strong> <em>Jesus Christ is strongly contrasted with other high priests because he did not have to offer sacrifices for his own sins.</em></p>\n<h3>He is eternal</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:20\">HEB 6:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:6\">HEB 5:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:17\">HEB 7:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:21\">HEB 7:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:28\">HEB 7:28</a></p>\n<h3>His atoning work was completed once for all</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:27\">HEB 7:27</a></strong> <em>Other high priests had to repeat their sacrifices.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:12\">HEB 9:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:25-Heb9:26\">HEB 9:25–9:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:28\">HEB 9:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:10\">HEB 10:10</a></p>\n<h3>He is exalted</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:1\">HEB 8:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech6:13\">ZEC 6:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:26\">HEB 7:26</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's high priesthood was of the order of Melchizedek</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:20\">HEB 6:20</a></strong> <em>The priesthood of Melchizedek resembles that of Jesus Christ because he too was king and had neither beginning nor end.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps110:4\">PSA 110:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:6\">HEB 5:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:10\">HEB 5:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:1-Heb7:4\">HEB 7:1–7:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:14-Heb7:17\">HEB 7:14–7:17</a></p>\n<h2>Responses to Jesus Christ's high priesthood</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:14-Heb4:15\">HEB 4:14–4:15</a> <em>a call to keep to the faith</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:16\">HEB 4:16</a> <em>an invitation to seek God's help in times of need</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:19-Heb10:22\">HEB 10:19–10:22</a> <em>an invitation to draw near to God</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:1-Heb12:3\">HEB 12:1–12:3</a> <em>a call to run the race of faith</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:28-Heb12:29\">HEB 12:28–12:29</a> <em>a call to offer thanksgiving and worship</em></p>",
